Build a RAG with Claude Code: From User Stories to a Multi-Domain AI Assistant

***

In this video, I walk through the complete setup of a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system built entirely with Claude Code, from initial idea to working prototype.

The project starts from simple user stories and evolves into a practical AI assistant usable across multiple domains:
- Journalism
- Human Resources (HR)
- RFP (Request for Proposal)
- Screenwriting

The key idea behind this RAG is not just answering questions, but enabling a human expert to navigate a dense corpus of information while preserving traceability of sources.

This video focuses on:
- Structuring a RAG pipeline from scratch
- Using Claude Code as the sole development assistant
- Managing token consumption efficiently during development
- Transforming raw content into a usable knowledge base

This is part of a broader experiment: building a complete AI product without traditional coding workflows, relying fully on Claude Code.

